properties.Name: StorageTank
properties.Description: A container that contains liquids, gases or compressed gases.

Columns.Name: StorageTankId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Storage Tank.

Columns.Name: StorageTankDescription
Columns.Description: A description of the storage tank.

Columns.Name: StorageTankTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankManufacturerName
Columns.Description: The name of the storage tank manufacturer.

Columns.Name: StorageTankConstructionCompletedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the storage tank construction is completed.

Columns.Name: StorageTankInstallationDate
Columns.Description: The date that the storage tank was installed.

Columns.Name: LastTestedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the storage tank was last tested.

Columns.Name: NextTestDate
Columns.Description: The next test date of the storage tank.

Columns.Name: StorageTankNumberOfWalls
Columns.Description: The number of walls comprising the storage tank.

Columns.Name: StorageTankColorDescription
Columns.Description: The color of the storage tank, which may be multiple colors - thus the need for a description.

Columns.Name: StorageTankNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the storage tank.

Columns.Name: ThermalStorageTankIndicator
Columns.Description: One form of seasonal thermal energy storage (STES) is the use of large surface water tanks that are insulated and then covered with earth berms to enable the year-round of solar-thermal heat that is collected primarily in the summer for all-year heating.[3] A related technology has become widespread in Danish district heating systems. The thermal storage medium is gravel and water in large, shallow, lined pits that are covered with insulation, soil and grass.[4]

Columns.Name: StorageTankStaticGroundingWireIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has a static grounding wire.

Columns.Name: AtmosphericTankIndicator
Columns.Description: An atmospheric tank is a container for holding a liquid at atmospheric pressure. The major design code for welded atmospheric tanks are API 650 and API 620. API 653 is used for analysis of in-service storage tanks. In Europe the design code is Eurocode 3 (EN 1993), part 4-2.

Columns.Name: StorageTankAutomaticMeasuringTubeIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank as an automatic measuring tube.

Columns.Name: StorageTankGroundLineOnRoofIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has a ground line on the roof.

Columns.Name: StorageTankAntiRotationCableWiringIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has anti-rotation cable wire.

Columns.Name: StorageTankFoamExtinguisherIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has an integrated foam extinguisher system.

Columns.Name: StorageTankEdgeBuoyIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has an edge buoy.

Columns.Name: StorageTankSupportColumnIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has a support column.

Columns.Name: StorageTankVacuumValveIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has a vacuum valve.

Columns.Name: StorageTankFloatingWellIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank has a float well.

Columns.Name: StorageTankMaximumTankLifeYears
Columns.Description: The storage tank maximum tank life expressed in years.

Columns.Name: StorageTankAboveGroundIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank is an above ground storage tank.

Columns.Name: StorageTankUndergroundIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the storage tank is an underground storage tank.

Columns.Name: StorageTankFloatingRoofIndicator
Columns.Description: Some storage tanks need a floating roof in addition to or in lieu of the fixed roof and structure. This floating roof rises and falls with the liquid level inside the tank, thereby decreasing the vapor space above the liquid level. Floating roofs are considered a safety requirement as well as a pollution prevention measure for many industries including petroleum refining.

Columns.Name: StorageTankCathodicProtectionIndicator
Columns.Description: In the United States, metal tanks in contact with soil and containing petroleum products must be protected from corrosion to prevent escape of the product into the environment.[2] The most effective and common corrosion control techniques for steel in contact with soil is cathodic protection.

Columns.Name: StorageTankElectronicMonitoredIndicator
Columns.Description: A probe permanently installed in the tank is wired to a monitor to provide information on product level and temperature. These systems automatically calculate the changes in product volume that can indicate a leaking tank and usually include a daily printout.

Columns.Name: StorageTankInterstitialMonitoringIndicator
Columns.Description:
Monitors are used to check the area between the tank and the barrier for leaks and alert the operator if a leak is suspected. 

Some monitors indicate the physical presence of the leaked product, either liquid or gaseous. Other monitors check for a change in condition that indicates a hole in the tank, such as a loss of vacuum or a change in the level of a monitoring liquid between the walls of a double-walled
tank.  

Monitors can be as simple as a dipstick used at the lowest point of the containment to see if liquid product has leaked and pooled there. Monitors can also be sophisticated automated systems that continuously check for leaks. If the system is equipped with an electronic
sensor, an alarm will sound and it will shut down the system if a leak is detected.

Columns.Name: StorageTankVaporMonitoringIndicator
Columns.Description: Vapor monitoring measures product "fumes" in the soil around the UST to check for a leak. This method requires installation of carefully placed monitoring wells. Vapor monitoring can be performed manually on a periodic basis or continuously using permanently installed equipment.

Columns.Name: StorageTankContainmentSumpIndicator
Columns.Description: A liquid-tight compartment enclosing the piping connections at the top of an UST providing containment of product leaks. If equipped with a sensor an alarm will sound when a leak is detected.

Columns.Name: StorageTankRoofTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank roof type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankFireSystemTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank fire system type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankMaterialTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank material type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankPipeConstructionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank pipe construction type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankShapeTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank shape type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankLeakDetectionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank leak detection type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankClassificationTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank classification type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankConstructionMaterialTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a storage tank construction material type.

Columns.Name: StorageTankLengthMeters
Columns.Description: The storage tank length in meters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankWidthMeters
Columns.Description: The storage tank width in meters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankHeightMeters
Columns.Description: The storage tank height in meters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankInnerDiameterMeters
Columns.Description: The storage tank inner diameters in meters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankVolumeCubicLiters
Columns.Description: The storage tank volume in cubic liters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankWeightTons
Columns.Description: The weight of the storage tank in tons.

Columns.Name: StorageTankWallThicknessMillimeters
Columns.Description: The storage tank wall thickness in millimeters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankOuterDiameterMeters
Columns.Description: Storage Tank outer Diameter Meters

Columns.Name: StorageTankContainmentDikeCircumferenceMeters
Columns.Description: The circumference of the storage tank containment dike in meters.

Columns.Name: StorageTankContainmentDikeHeightMeters
Columns.Description: The storage tank containment dike height in meters.

Columns.Name: InterstitialSpaceMillimeters
Columns.Description:
The space between the inner and outer walls of a  double walled tank or a secondary containment system in millimeters.

 May also be called "annular" space.

Columns.Name: StorageTankMaximumOperatingTemperatureC
Columns.Description: The maximum operating temperature of the storage tank in C.

Columns.Name: StorageTankMinimumOperatingTemperatureC
Columns.Description: The minimum operating temperature of the storage tank in C.

Columns.Name: StorageTankWallInterstitialSpaceMillimeters
Columns.Description:
The space between the inner and outer walls of a  double walled tank or a secondary containment system in millimeters.

 May also be called "annular" space.
